{"@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "HowTo", "name": "DIY First Birthday Hat for Girls", "description": "Make a super easy-to-wear first birthday hat using a little felt and some tulle! Customize the colors to suit any theme.", "estimatedCost": {"@type": "MonetaryAmount", "value": "0"}, "totalTime": "PT0S", "tool": [{"@type": "HowToTool", "name": "Good, thick felt sheet"}, {"@type": "HowToTool"}, {"@type": "HowToTool", "name": "6-7 inch round plate to trace"}, {"@type": "HowToTool", "name": "Ruler"}, {"@type": "HowToTool", "name": "Tailor's chalk"}, {"@type": "HowToTool", "name": "Fabric scissors"}, {"@type": "HowToTool"}, {"@type": "HowToTool", "name": "Hot glue gun"}], "step": [{"@type": "HowToSection", "name": "Trace your plate and make a roughly 7 inch circle.", "position": "1"}, {"@type": "HowToSection", "name": "Measure a line on the radius of the circle (half the width/diameter).", "position": "2"}, {"@type": "HowToSection", "name": "Cut off a bit more than half of the circle. It doesn't have to be exact - you'll be able to play with the shape in the next step and make a larger or smaller seam as you'd like.", "position": "3"}, {"@type": "HowToSection", "name": "Fold it in half and glue the straight edge together to form a seam. Make sure the cone is in a proportion that you like.", "position": "4"}, {"@type": "HowToSection", "name": "When it dries, trim the seam if necessary and turn your hat right side out.", "position": "5"}, {"@type": "HowToSection", "name": "Trim around the base.", "position": "6"}, {"@type": "HowToSection", "name": "Make your pom pom. Mine was deliberately oversized in proportion to the hat. Tulle is a lightweight material so it can handle it. I used a different method however I recommend you learn how to make a pom pom with tulle here and use that method.", "position": "7"}, {"@type": "HowToSection", "name": "Place some glue on the tip of the cone and attach it to the core of the pom pom.", "position": "8"}, {"@type": "HowToSection", "position": "9"}, {"@type": "HowToSection", "name": "Trace a circle a tiny bit smaller (like 1mm) than the base of your cone.", "position": "10"}, {"@type": "HowToSection", "name": "And glue it to the base of your first birthday hat.", "position": "11"}, {"@type": "HowToSection", "name": "Attach an elastic to fit around your baby's head and cover it with a smaller piece of felt to hide the elastic seam. This makes it more comfortable to wear too.", "position": "12"}]}